<item><title>RPQS 56-26 Design, Creative, Digital, Multimedia, Print &amp; Marketing Services</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Gladstone Regional Council (GRC) seeks to establish a Register of Pre-Qualified Suppliers (RPQS) comprising suitably qualified Service Providers for a range of digital media services.<br /><br />GRC periodically engages suitably experienced and qualified Service Providers to provide professional digital media, design, marketing, and print services to support GRC’s internal and external communication objectives. These services support a wide range of GRC activities, including community engagement, corporate communications, public awareness campaigns, events, and branding initiatives.<br /><br />The services may be required on an as-needed basis and may include, but are not limited to, the following categories:<br /><br />•	Graphic Design Support Services<br /><br />Provision of creative design services to support GRC’s visual communication needs, including the development of artwork and layouts for print, digital, signage, and online platforms, in accordance with GRC’s branding and communication objectives.<br...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Gladstone Regional Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 28/Jul/2026 05:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP515547<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Advertising and Media Services, Graphical, Photographic & Art, Marketing & Communications, Printing & Distribution Services<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 0]]></description>
<link>https://www.vendorpanel.com.au/PublicTenderAccess.aspx?id=b168d96e6c764e8ab3f0a758f495e11ds515547</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">b168d96e6c764e8ab3f0a758f495e11d</guid>
<pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 19:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
<category>Advertising and Media Services</category>
<category>Graphical, Photographic &amp; Art</category>
<category>Marketing &amp; Communications</category>
<category>Printing &amp; Distribution Services</category>
</item>
<item><title>TEN/3028 - Water Meter Reading Services</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Bundaberg Regional Council Water Services is responsible for the provision of quality, cost effective and environmentally sustainable operations of the water supply for residents of the Bundaberg Region, within 8 declared water areas, distributed through 956 km of reticulation, and metered through a fleet of approximately 38,000 water meters.<br /><br />The water meter fleet is a valuable asset group, as a water meter is used for calculating charges for customers usage by metering water consumption and providing insights into the consumption profile of the respective areas. The meter reading is conducted twice a year, in two (2) cycles and non-cyclic special reads for property transaction/conveyancing purposes of other Council business needs.<br /><br />This invitation to offer seeks to engage a suitably qualified and experienced Respondent to read the water meters for Council.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Bundaberg Regional Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 28/Jul/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP515568<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Utilities<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 2]]></description>
<link>https://www.vendorpanel.com.au/tsi.axd?id=b5ac4f9e0d454b5ca0bc3294ef10d5e7s515568sc7f4c031498943fbb1aef808c6fbc4das2921</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">b5ac4f9e0d454b5ca0bc3294ef10d5e7</guid>
<pubDate>Fri, 03 Jul 2026 19:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
<category>Utilities</category>
</item>
<item><title>TRC000551 Supply and delivery of bulk sodium hypochlorite</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The quantity of sodium hypochlorite required will depend on factors such as water quality and production but is estimated at 500,000 litres per annum.<br /><br />Product supplied shall be in accordance with requirements of this specification, by having 10% weight/volume minimum concentration of available chlorine.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Toowoomba Regional Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 28/Jul/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP515579<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Chemicals, Biochemical, Gas<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 7]]></description>
