<item><title>Design and Construction of the Aurukun Treated Water Reservoir</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> This project will ensure a fit for purpose long term solution for water infrastructure to meet current and future water demand for the community. The water infrastructure is critical in supplying safe and reliable potable water across the community of Aurukun.<br /><br />Please refer to the Specification which defines the scope of works and detailed requirements for the construction of a new treated water reservoir and pumpstation in Aurukun. The works include, but is not limited to, associated mechanical, geotechnical, civil, structural, and electrical components. This specification is to be read in conjunction with the scope of works, project drawings, and all relevant standards.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Dept of Local Government Water and Volunteers<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 07/Aug/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP515629<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Building Trade, Repairs, Maint., Construction & Operation, Utilities, Water & Sewage<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 10]]></description>
