<item><title>RFT2526-24 - Rates Support Services</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The Town of Port Hedland requires support to the Rates Team to enable compliant rates billing in a complex statutory environment. The roles include:<br /><br />•	Overseeing Annual Rate Setting<br /><br />•	Property Revaluations processes from Landgate<br /><br />•	Interim Rating<br /><br />•	A strong understanding on local government rating legislation, including Mining leases, State Agreements, Mining tenements, Pastoral leases, leasing and licenses as<br />described by the Mining Act (Mining Act 1904) and The Government Trading Enterprises Act 2023 (WA) (GTE Act) is required.<br /><br />•	An understanding of TechnologyOne Property and Rating module is also required.<br /><br />•	Transfer of knowledge to Rates and Finance team<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Town of Port Hedland<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 24/Jul/2026 05:00 PM (UTC+08:00) Perth time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP515607<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : IT & Telecomms<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 2]]></description>
