<item><title>Landslip Remediation Package 14</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Kempsey Shire Council invites qualified contractors to submit tenders for landslip remediation works aimed at restoring infrastructure, road safety and implementing slope stability measures following severe weather events. The package includes seven sites.<br /><br />A package of seven sites require works with the objective of:<br /><br /> - Stabilise and repair identified high-side and low-side embankment slips, realign pavement, culvert repair to restore road safety and functionality.<br /><br /> - Implement engineered solutions that address both immediate hazards and long-term slope stability.<br /><br /> - Minimise disruption to road users during construction through effective traffic management.<br /><br /> - Incorporate sustainable and resilient design to withstand future weather events and reduce maintenance needs.<br /><br /> - Comply with all relevant standards including geotechnical, environmental and workplace safety requirements.<br /><br />Further details are seen in tender documents available fo...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Kempsey Shire Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 28/Jul/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP515183<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Construction & Operation<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 12]]></description>
