<item><title>Prepare Temora Urban Release Areas Servicing Plan</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The project involves the delivery of a servicing plan to support major urban land release areas in Temora, to fast track the supply of development-ready housing land. The study area covers an area of 110 hectares and has the potential to support the delivery of 500 additional residential lots.<br /><br />The project objectives are to: <br /><br />-	Respond to the objectives of the Temora Local Housing Strategy, to support a range of housing opportunities, <br /><br />-	Build upon the existing momentum of housing delivery in Temora, ensuring there continues to be a ready supply of developable residential land, <br /><br />-	Complete concept investigations of the servicing requirements for short term priority projects identified within the Temora Local Housing Strategy 2026, <br /><br />-	Identify constraints within existing sewer and stormwater networks and define the enabling trunk infrastructure required for future development, <br /><br />-	Provide a strategy for the provision of servicing infrastructure, i...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Temora Shire Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 21/Jul/2026 05:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP515138<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Architecture, Design, Planning, Construction & Operation, Engineer, Research, Tech services, Environmental & Heritage Services, Water & Sewage<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 4]]></description>
