<item><title>Corporate Uniform, Workwear and Personal Protective Equipment under a Panel Contract Arrangement</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The City of Greater Bendigo (City) is seeking to form a panel of suppliers for the supply of corporate uniform, workwear and personal protective equipment (PPE) as required by City staff.<br /><br />The City has a workforce of approximately 1,000 staff, operating under both corporate and partner logos. The corporate uniform is compulsory for a number of staff and optional for the rest of the corporate workforce.<br /><br />The workwear uniform is compulsory for all outdoor workers.<br /><br />PPE will be purchased and provided to employees as required.<br /><br />Please refer to tender documents for full details.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Greater Bendigo City Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 21/Jul/2026 03:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP514523<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Clothing & Safety Equipment, Fire & Safety<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 6]]></description>
