<item><title>TRC000568 Pre-employment and fit for purpose medical assessments</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> In accordance with the Work Health and Safety Act 2011 Council has a duty of care to ensure that workers engaged by Council are not put at risk from work carried out as part of their role with the organisation. This duty of care also extends to other workers and members of the public who engage in services conducted by Council.<br /><br />To meet this obligation, Council requires all newly engaged employees to undertake a pre-employment fit for purpose medical assessment to ensure that they are medically fit to undertake the full requirements of their position with Council. Further, from time to time, it is also necessary for Council to seek professional assessments on the medical fitness of existing workers to undertake the full range of duties in their position with the organisation. This assessment may include independent specialist advice from suitably qualified service providers such as occupational therapists and occupational physicians.<br /><br />Council is seeking two main services from this tender: ...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Toowoomba Regional Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 21/Jul/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP514808<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Healthcare Services<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 7]]></description>
<link>https://www.vendorpanel.com.au/tsi.axd?id=e31e5edfef8341e899d7ca42b8a47987s514808s99858359486b4d3899bc47a81cfe4df4s1573</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">e31e5edfef8341e899d7ca42b8a47987</guid>
<pubDate>Fri, 26 Jun 2026 19:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
<category>Healthcare Services</category>
</item>
<item><title>2026/77 Ashburton Pool and Recreation Centre - Plant Room Upgrade</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> This project involves the staged upgrade of the pool plant systems at Ashburton Pool and Recreation Centre, comprising a controls upgrade and ozone decommissioning across the indoor 25m pool, outdoor 25m pool, hydrotherapy pool and spa systems, together with filtration system upgrades for the indoor 25m pool and outdoor 25m pool.<br /><br />The works include temporary measures required to maintain operations where necessary, decommissioning and removal of redundant ozone infrastructure, upgrades to the MechMate control system including PLC and HMI improvements, installation and integration of standalone water chemistry controllers, replacement of filtration equipment for the nominated pools including filters, pumps, strainers, variable speed drives, associated pipework, valves and manifolds, installation of UV secondary disinfection systems, associated electrical and instrumentation works, flow monitoring, testing, commissioning, operator training, handover, manuals, warranties and defects liability maintenan...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> City of Boroondara<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 17/Jul/2026 05:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP514841<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Gas Energy, Infrastructure, Equipment, Mechanical Plant, Equip, Services<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 1]]></description>
