<item><title>Performance Health Practitioner Services (Physiotherapy) - Paddle (Gold Coast)</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> QAS is seeking a qualified Sports and Exercise Physiotherapist to provide physiotherapy services to all National Training Centre (NTC) athletes and coaches across all the Paddle Australia (PA) High Performance Programs, and the underpinning QAS Paddle Program. The successful practitioner will also be responsible for developing strategies to support exceptional High-Performance outcomes. <br /><br />Services will be delivered across Paddle Australia’s Complex at Pizzey Park on the Gold Coast and other affiliated training facilities. <br /><br />The contract requires a commitment equivalent to four days per week. Services may be scheduled flexibly to meet program and athlete requirements and will be provided for 48 weeks in each 12-month period. The proposed contract term is from September 2026 to 25 February 2029.<br /><br />Responses are sought from individual practitioner/s who have the appropriate qualifications, experience, expertise and capacity to provide the required services.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Queensland Academy of Sport<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 20/Jul/2026 05:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP514779<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Healthcare Services<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 3]]></description>
