<item><title>C694 Annual Reseals 2026-2031</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The Council is seeking Tenders from appropriately qualified and experienced contractors for Bituminous Spray Sealing within the Loddon Shire Council. The Contract will be a schedule of rates contract subject to price adjustment for rise and fall in the rates over a two-year period with the option of up to three additional years on a 1 + 1 + 1 basis. (2 + 1 + 1+ 1). <br /><br />Quantum of spend over the next two-year period is approximately $2,250,000 with $750,000 allocated to 2026/27 financial year, subject to road condition assessments each year.<br /><br />The list of roads to be sealed in year 1 will be available from July/August 2026 and 30 June 2027, 2028, 2029 and 2030 for year 2/3/4/5. Roads are expected to be sealed prior to the end of January 2027 and December 2028, 2029, 2030 and 2031.<br /><br />This tender sets out the Works to comply with VicRoads standard sections 161, 166, 199, 310, 408, 710, 721, 802, and 831.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Loddon Shire Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 15/Jul/2026 12:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP514729<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Building Products & Materials, Construction & Operation<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 9]]></description>
<link>https://www.vendorpanel.com.au/PublicTenderAccess.aspx?id=8d33106669c34b1394c11fcaac95f091s514729</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">8d33106669c34b1394c11fcaac95f091</guid>
<pubDate>Thu, 25 Jun 2026 05:53:00 GMT</pubDate>
<category>Building Products &amp; Materials</category>
<category>Construction &amp; Operation</category>
</item>
<item><title>Neuro Wellness Hubs</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> This Invitation to Offer is for the establishment of eight (8) Neuro Wellness Hubs (Hubs), providing a coordinated model of care for Queenslanders experiencing neurological health conditions, and the delivery of the neuro community navigator program.<br /><br />The Neuro Wellness Hubs will provide a community-based space to deliver neuro wellness services, resources and information to people with neurological conditions (and their families/support network), and complement the services provided by acute speciality teams, general practice and other primary care services.<br /><br />The neuro community navigators’ program will support system navigation by connecting people with neurological conditions to broader systems including (but not limited to) the National Disability Insurance Scheme (NDIS), My Aged Care, Medicare and mental health services. <br /><br />The Queensland Government is seeking the establishment of Hubs in the following regions:<br /><br />• Townsville (Townsville Hospital and Health Service (...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Queensland Health<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 27/Jul/2026 10:00 AM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP514561<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Community & Social Services, Healthcare Services<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 5]]></description>
<link>https://www.vendorpanel.com.au/PublicTenderAccess.aspx?id=9c26ead8c6ec4e8c8e73b4327d1efae9s514561</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">9c26ead8c6ec4e8c8e73b4327d1efae9</guid>
<pubDate>Thu, 25 Jun 2026 05:16:00 GMT</pubDate>
<category>Community &amp; Social Services</category>
<category>Healthcare Services</category>
</item>
<item><title>Ross Lane Flood Resilience Betterment</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Ballina Shire Council is seeking to engage a Contractor for the betterment of a flood prone section of Ross Lane, Kinvara. This betterment project includes raising low portions of Ross Lane and the inclusion of a new bridge structure.<br /><br />Road Construction will include shoulder widening to provide 1.2m wide shoulders and improved structural performance through the addition of new, overlayed pavement layers. An existing triple cell culvert located at Deadman's Creek will be replaced with a single span concrete bridge structure to provide increased waterway area.<br /><br />Undertaking these works will improve the flood resilience of this arterial road and reduce the future impacts on the local and wider community.<br /><br />Tenderers should note that there is a pre-tender meeting held in accordance with the information provided in the 'Title Page' document. Attendance at this meeting is considered a mandatory requirement for a company to lodge a tender.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Ballina Shire Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 27/Jul/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP514639<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Construction & Operation<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 9]]></description>
