<item><title>201129 Water and Soil Quality Sampling and Analysis Services</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> A requirement exists to appoint N.A.T.A. registered laboratories, to provide soil and water quality sampling, laboratory analysis and reporting services to Council. Council conducts regular water quality monitoring programs and are also required to test water quality during day to day operations on an as needs basis. Council also undertakes soil sampling to assist Council Operations and Project Delivery Teams.<br /><br />The various water quality testing requirements conducted by Council during the year may include, but are not limited to the following projects:<br /><br />Strategic Water Monitoring Program (SWMP)<br /><br />Stormwater Quality Improvement Device (SQIDs) monitoring<br /><br />Recreational Monitoring Program<br /><br />Receiving Water Monitoring Program<br /><br />The Ridge Irrigation Monitoring Program<br /><br />Miscellaneous analysis<br /><br />Successful Tenderers will form a panel of preferred suppliers, with selected works and projects subject to a further competitive quotation process.<b...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Sutherland Shire Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 24/Jul/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP513460<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Chemicals, Biochemical, Gas, Engineer, Research, Tech services, Environmental & Heritage Services, Lab, Measure, Observe & Test Equip<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 4]]></description>
