<item><title>Parking Ticket Machine Supply and Maintenance</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The City of Vincent is seeking to engage a suitably qualified and experienced organisation to provide supply and maintenance to the parking ticket machines. The City currently operates 171 ticket machines across a range of paid and non-paid, on-street and off-street parking locations throughout the City. The City is seeking tenders from a suitably qualified and experienced contractor to deliver preventative and reactive maintenance services for these ticket machines for a period of three years.<br /><br />Please refer to the attached Request for Tender document for all information including how to respond.<br /><br />The closing time and date for all submissions is 2:00pm (WST) Wednesday 22 July 2026.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> City of Vincent<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 22/Jul/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+08:00) Perth time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP514053<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Jeremy Chalmers Email: jeremy.chalmers@vincent.wa.gov.au Tel: +61892736517<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Parking, Traffic Services & Equip<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 3]]></description>
