<item><title>QBCC Portal Phase 4</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The Queensland Building and Construction Commission (QBCC) is seeking to replace its existing customer portal (myQBCC) with a modern, scalable, and maintainable digital platform that enhances user experience, streamlines business operations, and positions QBCC for future digital transformation.<br /><br />We are seeking to engage a qualified supplier to expand the new QBCC customer portal to deliver the remaining portal features and functions, with a focus on:? <br /><br />•	expanding licence application online processing beyond owner-builder;? <br /><br />•	enabling end-to-end licence lifecycle management (e.g., renewals, variations, suspensions and cancellations);? <br /><br />•	uplifting identity management (including alignment with Queensland Digital Identity (QDI), Australian Government myID (myID), and multi-factor authentication approaches);? <br /><br />•	implementing additional external verification integrations where available (e.g., course/qualification validation and checks such as National Police...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Queensland Building and Construction Commission<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 13/Jul/2026 09:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP514207<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : IT & Telecomms<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 12]]></description>
