<item><title>Request for Tender CT2026069 Humula Bridge Replacement Design &amp; Construct</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> PROJECT:<br /><br />This work involves design and construction of a new bridge over Carabost Creek on Eight Mile Rd 500m west of Humula. The tender will also include the removal of the existing bridge and reinstatement of the road realignment of the Eight Mile Rd starting from and including Carabost Rd and Eight Mile Rd Intersection to Downfall Rd and Eight Mile Rd intersection as well as all the disturbed area . Council has assessed the service level required of the bridge and decided that the deck level for the new bridge should be similar or slightly higher than the existing timber deck level, and provide 7.0m clear traffic width. <br /><br />A new bridge should be approximately 40m long, ideally with 3 spans (assuming vertical abutments) with the central span being as long as economically viable to provide the largest opening for flood flows in the creek. <br /><br />The bridge should provide 7m clear carriageway width. After the existing bridge is removed rock fill should be placed across the creek at be...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Wagga Wagga City Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 27/Jul/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP514187<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Construction & Operation<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 14]]></description>
