<item><title>CN2025/120 - Kerbside Bin Lid Standarisation Project - Supply and Install</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The City of Boroondara Council is located in the inner eastern suburbs of Melbourne, between 5 and 10 kilometres east of the Melbourne CBD. <br /><br />The Victorian Government’s Circular Economy (waste Reduction and Recycling) Act 2021 contains policies for the standardisation of residential bin services, including bin lid colours. Boroondara will achieve compliance by changing the body-coloured general waste bin lids to red.<br /><br />Tenders are being sought from suitably qualified and experienced organisations for the procurement of bin lids, replacement bins, where applicable, and performing of the changeover at the associated properties.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> City of Boroondara<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 31/Jul/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP513836<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Rebecca Bogacz Email: rebecca.bogacz@boroondara.vic.gov.au Tel: 03 9278 4310<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Waste Management & Landfill<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 2]]></description>
