<item><title>Stuarts Point Sewerage Scheme - Construction of Pressure Sewer Network</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Kempsey Shire Council is inviting Expressions of Interest (EOI) for the construction of pressure sewer system (PSS). This package of works is part of the Stuarts Point Sewerage Scheme, which is being delivered as part of Council's broader Water and Sewer Program of Works.<br /><br />Construction works include civil, mechanical, hydraulic, plumbing and electrical aspects. This is relating to the construction, testing and commissioning of the pressure sewer network, on-property works, Grassy Head Sewage Pumping Station and Fishermans Reach Flushing Station.<br /><br />A mandatory site inspection is required on 03 July 2026.<br /><br />Refer to EOI documentation for all information.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Kempsey Shire Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 16/Jul/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP514007<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Construction & Operation<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 7]]></description>
