<item><title>Electronic Security Systems- Maintenance, Support and Upgrade Services</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The Port of Townsville is a critical piece of Queensland and Northern Australia’s trade, logistics, and supply chain infrastructure, operating within a geographically dispersed and operationally complex environment. The Port relies on a robust and integrated electronic security network to support safe operations, protect critical assets, manage access control, and meet regulatory, safety, and operational requirements.<br /><br />POTL’s existing security environment includes CCTV systems, video management platforms, access control systems, vehicle gates, and supporting network and power infrastructure installed across operational, leased, and third-party managed areas. Given the scale, diversity, and criticality of these systems, specialist technical support is required to ensure reliability, availability, and alignment with best practice.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Port of Townsville Limited<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 10/Jul/2026 10:00 AM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP513949<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Security Services & Equipment<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 7]]></description>
