<item><title>Peak Crossing Transfer Station – Office and Amenities upgrade</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Scenic Rim Regional Council (‘Council’ or ‘Principal’) is inviting tenders from suitably qualified contractors to develop and finalise a design, obtain the building approvals and permits, and construct a new office and amenities building including associated electrical and hydraulic services for staff managing the Peak Crossing Transfer Station. The works are to be delivered on a design and construct basis, with the successful Contractor responsible for design, all regulatory approvals, construction, commissioning and handover. The works replace the existing demountable building and associated services. The scope also includes the supply and installation of a solar photovoltaic (PV) and battery system to service the facility through a locally nominated electrical subcontractor.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Scenic Rim Regional Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 10/Jul/2026 05:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP513974<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Building Products & Materials, Building Trade, Repairs, Maint., Construction & Operation<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 9]]></description>
