<item><title>Continuous Control Monitoring</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The University of Southern Queensland (UniSQ) invites suitably qualified Suppliers to submit an Offer for the provision of a Continuous Control Monitoring (CCM) solution.<br /><br />UniSQ currently undertakes control monitoring activities across key financial and people-related processes, including procure-to-pay (including corporate credit cards) and payroll, through a combination of manual and fragmented approaches. <br /><br />This limits the University’s ability to consistently identify control exceptions, anomalies, non-compliance and potential fraud in a timely and systematic manner.<br /><br />The objective of this Invitation to Offer is to implement a Continuous Control Monitoring (CCM) solution that strengthens oversight, risk detection, and assurance across critical business processes.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> University of Southern Queensland<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 10/Jul/2026 05:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP513996<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : IT & Telecomms<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 4]]></description>
<link>https://www.vendorpanel.com.au/tsi.axd?id=8005b00f26f64faebd1c51fb896c1cb6s513996se5e0fee99bee4eef813ebcd8f1872d76s1578</link>
