<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> QAS requires one or more sport psychologists to provide support to categorised podium, developing and emerging athletes within the QAS Skate and/or BMX Freestyle programs. Services will be delivered on the Gold Coast including the AusCycling National BMX Freestyle Park in Carrara, Skate Australia High Performance Centres including in Casuarina, and other affiliated training facilities.<br /><br />Supplier (practitioner) may submit a response for: <br /><br /> - Skate only –1 day per week; <br /><br /> - BMX Freestyle only –1.5 days per week; or <br /><br /> - Skate and BMX Freestyle –2.5 days per week.<br /><br />QAS reserves the right to award a contract for Skate, BMX Freestyle, or both sport programs to one or more Suppliers based on the evaluation outcome.<br /><br />Services may be scheduled flexibly to meet program and athlete requirements and will be provided for 48 weeks in each 12-month period. The proposed contract term is from 3 August 2026 to 25 February 2029.<br /><br />Responses are sought from ...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Queensland Academy of Sport<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 07/Jul/2026 05:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP513688<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Healthcare Services<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 3]]></description>
