<item><title>Executive Officer to the Regional Capitals Alliance Western Australia (RCAWA)</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The City of Bunbury has issued this request for the Western Australian Regional Capitals Alliance Incorporated.<br /><br />The Regional Capitals Alliance Western Australian (RCAWA) is seeking to appoint a suitably qualified consultant to perform the role of Executive Officer to the Alliance.<br /><br />As a guide, it is estimated the annual requirement to perform this function is approximately 400 hours and the appointment is for an initial two (2) year term. <br /><br />RCAWA has an important role to play in advancing regional Western Australia’s development and vibrant economic diversity through the promotion of effective collaboration, advocacy, strategic planning and forging effective partnerships that are aligned to the following vision:<br /><br />“RCAWA will enable the member regional capital communities to evolve into fully fledged alternatives to the Perth metropolitan areas.<br /><br />This is an outstanding opportunity to make a positive difference in regional development by leading the Alliance th...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> City of Bunbury<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 08/Jul/2026 05:00 PM (UTC+08:00) Perth time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP513651<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Business & Administrative Services, Engineer, Research, Tech services, Financial & Insurance Services, Management Advisory Services<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 3]]></description>
