<item><title>Q26057 - The Classics Opera – Artistic Direction Services</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Council is looking to engage the Artistic Direction services of an individual or organisation with strong experience in the delivery of concert style operatic performances. <br /><br />The Classics, Opera, Broadway, and Symphony comprised a long-running concert series. In recent years, program revisions have led to Opera becoming a standalone event held each February.<br /><br />As a result, it is proposed that the next iteration revert to the original title: Opera in the Park.<br /><br />Duties of this role will include but are not limited to:<br /><br />-	Creative programming including formation of operatic repertoire in keeping with the objectives of the event<br /><br />-	Submitting an artistic budget which includes the Artistic Director’s fee and the fees of all artists and any other creative staff <br /><br />-	Recruiting and working with a selection of artists (vocalists, musicians and MC) and any additional creative staff in consultation with the producers (City of Stonnington)<br /><br />-	Recruiting...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> City of Stonnington<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 17/Jul/2026 12:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP513531<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Event Management & Services, HR Services & Recruitment, Travel & Tourism<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 1]]></description>
