<item><title>2026/315 Provision of Kerbside Glass Crushing and Processing Services</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Mildura Rural City Council is seeking Tender responses from suitably qualified organisations to provide glass crushing and processing services for kerbside-collected glass arising from Council’s purple-lidded bin service.<br /><br />Council introduced a dedicated kerbside glass recycling service on 1 July 2024, providing 120-litre purple-lidded bins to residential properties within the kerbside collection boundary. This initiative forms part of the Victorian Government’s standardisation of household recycling across all 79 Victorian councils by 2027 (and no later than 2030), consistent with the requirements of the Circular Economy (Waste Reduction and Recycling) Act 2021 and the Recycling Victoria: A New Economy policy. (Note: In late 2025, the Victorian Government confirmed that Recycling Victoria will be merged with EPA Victoria.)<br /><br />By collecting glass separately from other recyclables (yellow-lidded bin), breakage and contamination of paper, cardboard and other materials is prevented, enabling hig...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Mildura Rural City Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 09/Jul/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP513196<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Construction & Operation, Waste Management & Landfill<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 9]]></description>
