<item><title>Works 4 Queensland Design and Construct Package</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Hinchinbrook Shire Council has secured funding under the Queensland Government’s Works for Queensland Program to deliver a package of community infrastructure projects across the Hinchinbrook Shire. The program is intended to enhance public recreational facilities, improve accessibility, support community wellbeing, and provide long-term benefits to residents and visitors through the renewal and development of key public assets.<br /><br />This Design and Construct Contract encompasses four separable portions located at Borello Park (Lucinda), Merv Whacker Park (Ingham), Leo Park (Trebonne), and Vince Corbett Park (Forrest Beach). The works comprise a combination of planning, community consultation, detailed design, approvals, and construction activities, ranging from playground and park upgrades through to the delivery of new recreational facilities and public amenities.<br /><br />The Principal seeks to engage a suitably qualified and experienced Contractor to provide a fully integrated Design and Construct...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Hinchinbrook Shire Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 06/Jul/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP513075<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Construction & Operation<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 9]]></description>
