</item>
<item><title>SSROC Shotcrete Stabilisation and Associated Services</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> SSROC, in collaboration with Participating Councils, is establishing a new Standing Agreement for the provision of shotcrete, stabilisation and associated services, including specialist enabling works and specialist wet hire, for assets managed by SSROC Member Councils.<br /><br />The Preferred Supplier(s) must demonstrate the capacity and capability to deliver specialist stabilisation works across a range of environments, including high-risk and emergency scenarios, and where required, provide specialist plant and operator services directly associated with stabilisation activities.<br /><br />The establishment of a pre-qualified regional Panel provides Member Councils with a compliant, risk-managed procurement mechanism to access appropriately qualified contractors for emergency, reactive and programmed maintenance works, where required, in a manner that aligns with each Council’s asset management objectives and governance responsibilities for these high-risk assets.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Sutherland Shire Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 10/Jul/2026 03:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP513056<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Construction & Operation, Plant & Equipment - Hire<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 6]]></description>
