<item><title>Small Business Grants initiative</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The Queensland Government via Customer, Small and Family Business within CDSB is preparing to release two related grant programs. <br /><br />The Construction and Professional Care Business Advancement Grants will provide up to $5,000 to eligible small businesses to adopt business management software and associated training. The programs aim to lift productivity, reduce administrative burden, and support small businesses to operate more efficiently.<br /><br />This Expression of Interest will assist the establishment of a catalogue of software suppliers to support these programs. The EOI closes on the 07/07/26. <br /><br />It is anticipated that the programs will be launched to small business sector later in 2026.<br /><br />Further information regarding the program, the catalogue and process can be viewed through the Business Queensland website at https://www.business.qld.gov.au/industries/science-it-creative/ict/business-software-catalogue/_nocache<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Customer, Data and Small Business (CDSB)<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 07/Jul/2026 05:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP513053<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : IT & Telecomms, Training & Development<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 1]]></description>
