<pubDate>Mon, 08 Jun 2026 04:40:00 GMT</pubDate>
<category>Graphical, Photographic &amp; Art</category>
<category>IT &amp; Telecomms</category>
</item>
<item><title>Forward Notification - North Johnstone Bridge Replacement</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> This notice is issued for informational purposes only. No Scope of Works or additional details are available at this time.<br /><br />A future tender will seek to engage a Principal Contractor to undertake the construction of the North Johnstone River Bridge Replacement project, which involves the construction of a new single track railway bridge over the North Johnstone River, approximately 4 km north of Innisfail on the North Coast Line (NCL) in Far North Queensland. <br /><br />The existing bridge, located at approximately chainage 1597.870 km, has been in service for approximately 100 years and currently supports both passenger and freight rail operations. Due to age related deterioration, increasing maintenance demands and ongoing structural performance concerns, Queensland Rail has initiated the replacement of the existing structure to ensure the continued safe and reliable operation of the rail network. <br /><br />The project has been developed as an offline bridge replacement to minimise disruption t...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Queensland Rail<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 10/Jul/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP512541<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Dayne Liebelt Email: dayne.liebelt@qr.com.au Tel: (07) 3096 0924<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Construction & Operation<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 2]]></description>
