<item><title>RFT260044 Regional Major Entertainment Venues - Theatre Improvement Works Upgrades</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Introduction<br /><br />The Central Highlands region is in Central Queensland, Australia. The region encompasses an area of around 60,000 square kilometres, making it just short of the size of Tasmania.<br /><br />It is home to around 30 000 people who live in the regional centre of Emerald (approximately 15,000 people) and twelve other unique communities being Arcadia Valley, Bauhinia, Blackwater, Bluff, Capella, Comet, Dingo, Duaringa, Emerald, Rolleston, Gemfields, Springsure and Tieri.<br /><br />Our region is rich in minerals and agriculture, thriving on irrigation sourced from water storage on the Nogoa and Comet rivers. We claim the largest sapphire-producing fields in the Southern Hemisphere.<br /><br />Major freight routes through the region include the north-south link between Charters Towers and northern New South Wales—identified as the inland transport alternative between Cairns and Melbourne.<br /><br />Central Highlands region has a road network of 4550km of council owned rural roads and urban ...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Central Highlands Regional Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 17/Jul/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP507126<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Audio Visual Photo Equip & Supp., Building Trade, Repairs, Maint., Construction & Operation, Domestic & Consumer ELEC, ELEC, Lighting, Equip & Services, Furniture & Furnishings<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 11]]></description>
