<item><title>RFT2526-25 Hamilton Road Upgrade and Landscaping</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The Town is seeking a suitability qualified Contractor to deliver the construction of the Hamilton Road upgrade and associated landscaping. The Hamilton Road upgrade includes the construction of two round-abouts and the required road realignment to connect with the new round-abouts.<br /><br />This upgrade is designed to improve safety and facilitate the seamless movement of vehicles and reduce traffic congestion during peak times. These round-abouts and road upgrade will form park of the first stage in the South Hedland Integrated Sports Hub development.<br /><br />It needs to be noted that a high number of services are located within the roading corridor of Hamilton Road, and care will be required in working around these services.<br /><br />The works will include the upgrading of the landscaping within the Hamilton Road corridor and the installation of irrigation infrastructure as designed. The landscaping is included to establish a unified design and cohesive aesthetics throughout the project area.<br /><...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Town of Port Hedland<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 17/Jul/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+08:00) Perth time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP508127<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Building Trade, Repairs, Maint., Construction & Operation, ELEC, Lighting, Equip & Services, Horticulture & Arboriculture<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 31]]></description>
